President Joe Biden spoke at an event celebrating the anniversary of the Americans with Disabilities Act. He thanked the advocates and activists who have worked to advance disability rights and make the country more accessible and just. Biden highlighted the importance of the Rehabilitation Act, which he co-sponsored as a senator, and the Americans with Disabilities Act. He acknowledged that there is still work to be done, such as improving employment opportunities and access to healthcare for disabled Americans. The President also discussed the actions his administration has taken to promote equality and equity for people with disabilities, including appointing disabled individuals to government positions and expanding funding for home- and community-based services. He emphasized the need for accessibility in all aspects of life and expressed optimism about the future progress that can be made.